description: Describes an existing export job. Poll job descriptions after a job starts to know the status of the job. When a job succeeds, a URL is provided to download the exported assets' data from. Download URLs are valid for five minutes after they are generated. You can call the DescribeAssetBundleExportJob API for a new download URL as needed. Job descriptions are available for 14 days after the job starts.

parameters.name: AwsAccountId
parameters.description: The ID of the Amazon Web Services account the export job is executed in.

parameters.name: AssetBundleExportJobId
parameters.description: The ID of the job that you want described. The job ID is set when you start a new job with a StartAssetBundleExportJob API call.

nested_items.name: JobStatus
nested_items.description: Indicates the status of a job through its queuing and execution.

nested_items.name: DownloadUrl
nested_items.description: The URL to download the exported asset bundle data from.

nested_items.name: Errors
nested_items.description: An array of error records that describes any failures that occurred during the export job processing.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the resource whose processing caused an error.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The specific error type of the error that occurred.

nested_items.name: Message
nested_items.description: A description of the error.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the export job.

nested_items.name: CreatedTime
nested_items.description: The time that the export job was created.

nested_items.name: AssetBundleExportJobId
nested_items.description: The ID of the job. The job ID is set when you start a new job with a StartAssetBundleExportJob API call.

nested_items.name: AwsAccountId
nested_items.description: The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that the export job was executed in.

(string) ---

nested_items.description: The include dependencies flag.

nested_items.name: ExportFormat
nested_items.description: The format of the exported asset bundle. A QUICKSIGHT_JSON formatted file can be used to make a StartAssetBundleImportJob API call. A CLOUDFORMATION_JSON formatted file can be used in the CloudFormation console and with the CloudFormation APIs.

nested_items.name: PrefixForAllResources
nested_items.description: An option to request a CloudFormation variable for a prefix to be prepended to each resource's ID before import. The prefix is only added to the asset IDs and does not change the name of the asset.
